name: Teddy Afro
bio: Tewodros Kassahun, better known by his stage name of Teddy Afro, is an iconic Ethiopian pop star who has dominated the national music scene for the last decade and a half.

name: Aster Aweke
bio: Born in Gonder, near Lake Tana, Aster realized her passion for singing at a young age.  Today, her songs have become anthems to her fans in Ethiopia, as well as to Ethiopians living abroad.  She remains one of the Top female artists of our time.

name: Jacky Gosee
bio: Rising star Gossaye Kelemu (Jacky Gosee), has been capturing the hearts of many fans around the world.  With his traditional beats, catchy tunes, and strong stage presence he is building up to become an artist to be reckoned with, and also leave his mark on the Ethiopian music industry.

name: Eyob Mekonnen
bio:
The Jijiga born and raised, Eyob Mekonnen, heavily influenced by music from Ali Birra and Bob Marley was one to be reckoned with.  His most seductive sultry voice has romanced many Ethiopians, serenading all with his life inspired, emotionally compounded debut album, Ande Kal. 
[R.I.P] His legacy will live on!

name: Jano Band
bio: Jano formed in 2011 with the mission to transform traditional African music and to shape the future of rock â€˜n roll. Born and raised in Ethiopia, the bandâ€™s ten members share a musical passion with them since early childhood days.  Their soulful music focuses on the topics of love, adventure, loss and the journeys we all take through life, played with the Ethiopian rhythm of their youth as the backdrop to a new, vibrant rock sound.

name: Yegna
bio: Yegna is Ethiopia's first girl band and their music focuses on the social issues and concerns that appeal to Ethiopia's girls and women at large.  The band have followed up the success of their first hit single with Haile Roots, Abet, with more popular hits and radio dramas.

name: Mulatu Astatke
bio: An Ethiopian musician and arranger best known as the father of Ethio-jazz

name: Nati Haile
bio: Natiâ€™s love of music and singing began as a young boy growing up in Ethiopia where he sang solo in his Church Choir. He is known to have a magnificent voice that has been compared to very popular Ethiopian singers like Muluken Mellesse and Tewodros Taddesse.  After two successful albums, he is now finishing up his third album due to be released in early 2014.

name: Rasselas
bio: Born in the land of heritage and culture, Rasselas has been fortunate to grow up familiarized with tradition.  Currently residing in Canada, his work blends hip-hop with traditional Ethiopian music.  Rasselas new album will be titled "Traditional Food" and is well anticipated by the global Ethiopian community.

name: Theodros Mitiku
bio: One of the most talented and versatile Ethiopian musicians of our time.  He has been enthralling audiences with his unique playing style and mastery of the saxophone.   Teddy began his career with "The Ibex Band" in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia before coming to the US in 1983.  He had the first acoustic Ethiopian/Jazz blend record ever to be produced.  Teddy will be remembered as one of the greatest saxophonist and musician our country has produced.

name: Girma Wolde Michael
bio: Girma Wolde Michael has been playing professionally for various bands in Ethiopia for over fifteen years.

name: Sami Dan Betty G Jano Band Asge
Sami Dan | Betty G | Dawit Tsige | Esubalew Y
Tizitaw Samuel & Mirtnesh Tilahun & Zerfe Kebede
Meklit
bio: Meklit's music is imbued with poetry and multiplicity, from hybridized sounds of Tizita (haunting and nostalgic music) drawing from her Ethiopian heritage, to the annals of jazz, folk songs, hip-hop and art rock. She aptly describes her music as emanating from “in-between-spaces.” Listening to Meklit transports us to the post-national space of Africa and America, inspiring us to bridge the frontiers between language, tribes and disciplines. Her songs celebrate the newness of life and the hyphens that bring us together.

name: Ye-Natherth Wongel Berhan Church Solo Zemariwoch
Helena
bio: Ethiopian independent artist, lives art through song, dance and film. Artistic expressions through homemade creative works!
